President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Robert Stephen Ford as the Ambassador to the Syrian Arab Republic and Jonathan Andrew Hatfield as the Inspector General of the Corporation for National and Community Service. Ford is currently the Deputy Chief of Mission at the U.S. Embassy in Baghdad and has extensive experience in the Foreign Service. Hatfield is currently the Deputy Inspector General of the Federal Election Commission and has held various positions within the Office of Inspector General. Both nominees have received awards for their accomplishments in their respective fields.